The paper deals with the task of annotating images with semantic tuples, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed approach involves a factorized log-linear model, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenge of data sparsity, which is a common issue in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.MM.
